    {
      "id": "l5-ordering",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Asking for food",
      "body": "# Asking for food\n\nTwo useful phrases at a table or shop:\n\n- **I am hungry.** (मुझे भूख लगी है।)\n- **I want water.** (मुझे पानी चाहिए।)\n\nTo be more polite, add **please** (कृपया) at the end: *I want water, please.* In English the order is **subject + want + thing**: *I want tea* (मुझे चाय चाहिए), never *I tea want*."
    },
